                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00 Nanking/247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-31T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For the Minister. Department’s March 31, 1 p.m., your March 31, 8 p.m. Notes
                    which you have signed are satisfactory. Department has no further comments to
                    make.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
